cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.RO, cs.MM 

This paper deals with the problem of pedestrian detection using multispectral images, which involves computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) techniques. The proposed framework includes a region feature alignment module and a region of interest (RoI) jittering training strategy, which are both related to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and robotics (cs.RO). Additionally, the paper provides dense, high-quality, and modality-independent color-thermal annotation pairs, which can be useful for multimodal (cs.MM) research.
